      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The protocols supported by the Azure AD v2.0 app model public preview.",
      "pos": [
        78,
        148
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "App model v2.0 preview: Protocols - OAuth 2.0 &amp; OpenID Connect",
      "pos": [
        461,
        523
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The v2.0 app model provides identity-as-a-service for your apps by supporting industry standard protocols, OpenID Connect and OAuth 2.0.",
      "pos": [
        525,
        661
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "While the service is standard compliant, there can be subtle differences between any two implementations of these protocols.",
      "pos": [
        663,
        787
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The information here will be useful if you choose to write your code by directly sending &amp; handling HTTP requests, rather than using one of our open source libraries.",
      "pos": [
        789,
        955
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This information applies to the v2.0 app model public preview.",
      "pos": [
        1020,
        1082
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For instructions on how to integrate with the generally available Azure AD service, please refer to the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">Azure Active Directory Developer Guide](active-directory-developers-guide.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        1084,
        1267
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Tokens\nThe v2.0 app model's implementation of OAuth 2.0 and OpenID Connect make extensive use of bearer tokens, including bearer tokens represented as JWTs.",
      "pos": [
        1272,
        1428
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A bearer token is a lightweight security token that grants the “bearer” access to a protected resource.",
      "pos": [
        1429,
        1532
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In this sense, the “bearer” is any party that can present the token.",
      "pos": [
        1533,
        1601
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Though a party must first authenticate with Azure AD to receive the bearer token, if the required steps are not taken to secure the token in transmission and storage, it can be intercepted and used by an unintended party.",
      "pos": [
        1602,
        1823
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "While some security tokens have a built-in mechanism for preventing unauthorized parties from using them, bearer tokens do not have this mechanism and must be transported in a secure channel such as transport layer security (HTTPS).",
      "pos": [
        1824,
        2056
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If a bearer token is transmitted in the clear, a man-in the middle attack can be used by a malicious party to acquire the token and use it for an unauthorized access to a protected resource.",
      "pos": [
        2057,
        2247
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The same security principles apply when storing or caching bearer tokens for later use.",
      "pos": [
        2248,
        2335
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Always ensure that your  app transmits and stores bearer tokens in a secure manner.",
      "pos": [
        2336,
        2419
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more security considerations on bearer tokens, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">RFC 6750 Section 5](http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6750)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        2420,
        2532
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Further details of different types of tokens used in the v2.0 app model is available in <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">the v2.0 app model token reference](active-directory-v2-tokens.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        2534,
        2690
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The Basics\nEvery app that uses the v2.0 app model will need to be registered at <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">apps.dev.microsoft.com](https://apps.dev.microsoft.com)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        2695,
        2832
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The app registration process will collect &amp; assign a few values to your app:\n\n- An <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Application Id<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> that uniquely identifies your app\n- A <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Redirect URI<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> or <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Package Identifier<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept> that can be used to direct responses back to your app\n- A few other scenario-specific values.",
      "pos": [
        2834,
        3110
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more detail, learn how to <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">register an app](active-directory-v2-app-registration.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        3112,
        3201
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Once registered, the  app communicates with Azure AD my sending requests to the v2.0 endpoint:\n\n```\nhttps://login.microsoftonline.com/common/oauth2/v2.0/authorize\nhttps://login.microsoftonline.com/common/oauth2/v2.0/token\n```\n\nIn nearly all OAuth &amp; OpenID Connect flows, there are four parties involved in the exchange:\n\n<ph id=\"ph1\">![OAuth 2.0 Roles](../media/active-directory-v2-flows/protocols_roles.png)</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">\n\n-</ph> The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Authorization Server<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> is the v2.0 Endpoint.",
      "pos": [
        3203,
        3652
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It is responsible for ensuring the user's identity, granting and revoking access to resources, and issuing tokens.",
      "pos": [
        3654,
        3768
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It is also known as the identity provider - it securely handles anything to do with the user's information, their access, and the trust relationships between parties in an flow.",
      "pos": [
        3770,
        3947
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "- The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Resource Owner<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> is typically the end-user.",
      "pos": [
        3948,
        3999
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It is the party that owns the data, and has the power to allow third parties to access that data, or resource.",
      "pos": [
        4001,
        4111
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "- The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>OAuth Client<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> is your app, identified by its Application Id.",
      "pos": [
        4112,
        4181
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It is usually the party that the end-user interacts with, and it requests tokens from the authorization server.",
      "pos": [
        4183,
        4294
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The client must be granted permission to access the resource by the resource owner.",
      "pos": [
        4296,
        4379
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "- The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Resource Server<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> is where the resource or data resides.",
      "pos": [
        4380,
        4444
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It trusts the Authorization Server to securely authenticate and authorize the OAuth Client, and uses Bearer access_tokens to ensure that access to a resource can be granted.",
      "pos": [
        4446,
        4619
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "OAuth2 Authorization Code Flow\nThe OAuth 2.0 authorization code flow is described in in <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">section 4.1 of the OAuth 2.0 specification](http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        4624,
        4793
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It is used to perform authentication and authorization in the majority of  app types, including <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">web apps](active-directory-v2-flows.md#web-apps)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p2\">natively installed  apps](active-directory-v2-flows.md#mobile-and-native-apps)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        4795,
        5025
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It enables apps to securely acquire access_tokens which can be used to access resources that are secured using the v2.0 app model.",
      "pos": [
        5027,
        5157
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Here is the entire flow for a native  app; each request is detailed in the sections below:",
      "pos": [
        5161,
        5251
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">![OAuth Auth Code Flow](../media/active-directory-v2-flows/convergence_scenarios_native.png)</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">\n\n####</ph> Request an Authorization Code\nThe authorization code flow begins with the client directing the user to the <ph id=\"ph3\">`/authorize`</ph> endpoint.",
      "pos": [
        5252,
        5480
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In this request, the client indicates the permissions it needs to acquire from the user:\n\n```\nGET https://login.microsoftonline.com/common/oauth2/v2.0/authorize?",
      "pos": [
        5482,
        5643
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "client_id=2d4d11a2-f814-46a7-890a-274a72a7309e      // Your registered Application Id\n&amp;response_type=code\n&amp;redirect_uri=http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%2Fmyapp%2F       // Your registered Redirect Uri, url encoded\n&amp;response_mode=query                                  // 'query', 'form_post', or 'fragment'\n&amp;scope=                                            // See table below for scope parameter details.",
      "pos": [
        5644,
        6040
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "https%3A%2F%2Fgraph.windows.net%2Fdirectory.read%20\nhttps%3A%2F%2Fgraph.windows.net%2Fdirectory.write\n&amp;state=12345                                         // Any value provided by your app\n```\n\n| Parameter | | Description |\n| ----------------------- | ------------------------------- | ----------------------- |\n| client_id | required | The Application Id that the registration portal (<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">apps.dev.microsoft.com](https://apps.dev.microsoft.com)</ept>) assigned your app.",
      "pos": [
        6041,
        6503
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| response_type | required | Must include <ph id=\"ph1\">`code`</ph> for the authorization code flow.",
      "pos": [
        6504,
        6587
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| redirect_uri | required | The redirect_uri of your app, where authentication responses can be sent and receieved by your app.",
      "pos": [
        6588,
        6717
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It must exactly match one of the redirect_uris you registered in the portal, except it must be url encoded.",
      "pos": [
        6719,
        6826
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| scope | required | A space-separated list of scopes.",
      "pos": [
        6827,
        6883
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A single scope value indicates to the v2.0 endpoint both the resource and the permissions to that resource being requested.",
      "pos": [
        6885,
        7008
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Scopes take the form `",
      "pos": [
        7010,
        7032
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "/",
      "pos": [
        7052,
        7053
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`.  In the example above, the app identifier for the Azure AD Graph API is used, `</ph>https://graph.windows.net<ph id=\"ph2\">`, and two permissions are requested: `</ph>directory.read<ph id=\"ph3\">` and `</ph>directory.write`.",
      "pos": [
        7066,
        7250
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For a more detailed explanation of scopes, refer to c.",
      "pos": [
        7252,
        7306
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|",
      "pos": [
        7308,
        7309
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "| response_mode | recommended | Specifies the method that should be used to send the resulting authorization_code back to your app.",
      "pos": [
        7310,
        7441
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Can be one of 'query', 'form_post', or 'fragment'.",
      "pos": [
        7443,
        7493
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "| state | recommended | A value included in the request that will also be returned in the token response.",
      "pos": [
        7494,
        7599
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It can be a string of any content that you wish.",
      "pos": [
        7601,
        7649
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A randomly generated unique value is typically used for preventing cross-site request forgery attacks.",
      "pos": [
        7651,
        7753
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The state is also used to encode information about the user's state in the app before the authentication request occurred, such as the page or view they were on.",
      "pos": [
        7755,
        7916
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|",
      "pos": [
        7917,
        7918
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "| prompt | optional | Indicates the type of user interaction that is required.",
      "pos": [
        7919,
        7997
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The only valid value at this time is 'login', which forces the user to enter their credentials on that request.",
      "pos": [
        7999,
        8110
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Single-sign on will not take effect.",
      "pos": [
        8112,
        8148
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n\nAt this point, the user will be asked to enter their credentials and complete the authentication.",
      "pos": [
        8149,
        8249
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The v2.0 endpoint will also ensure that the user has consented to the permissions indicated in the <ph id=\"ph1\">`scope`</ph> query parameter.",
      "pos": [
        8251,
        8374
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If the user has not consented to any of those permissions, it will ask the user to consent to the required permissions.",
      "pos": [
        8376,
        8495
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Details of <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">permissions, consent, and multi-tenant apps are provided here](active-directory-v2-scopes.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        8497,
        8603
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Once the user authenticates and grants consent, the v2.0 endpoint will return a response to your app at the indicated <ph id=\"ph1\">`redirect_uri`</ph>, using the method specified in the <ph id=\"ph2\">`response_mode`</ph> parameter.",
      "pos": [
        8605,
        8799
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A successful response using <ph id=\"ph1\">`response_mode=query`</ph> looks like:\n\n```\nGET https://localhost/myapp/?",
      "pos": [
        8801,
        8897
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "code=AwABAAAAvPM1KaPlrEqdFSBzjqfTGBCmLdgfSTLEMPGYuNHSUYBrq...   // the authorization_code, truncated\n&amp;session_state=7B29111D-C220-4263-99AB-6F6E135D75EF            // a value generated by the v2.0 endpoint\n&amp;state=12345                                                                            // the value provided in the request\n```\n\n| Parameter | Description |\n| ----------------------- | ------------------------------- |\n| code | The authorization_code that the  app requested.",
      "pos": [
        8898,
        9380
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The  app can use the authorization code to request an access token for the target resource.",
      "pos": [
        9381,
        9472
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Authorization_codes are very short lived, typically they expire after about 10 minutes.",
      "pos": [
        9474,
        9561
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| session_state | A unique value that identifies the current user session.",
      "pos": [
        9562,
        9638
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This value is a GUID, but should be treated as an opaque value that is passed without examination.",
      "pos": [
        9639,
        9737
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| state | If a state parameter is included in the request, the same value should appear in the response.",
      "pos": [
        9738,
        9844
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The  app should verify that the state values in the request and response are identical.",
      "pos": [
        9845,
        9932
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n\nError responses may also be sent to the <ph id=\"ph1\">`redirect_uri`</ph> so the app can handle them appropriately:\n\n```\nGET https://localhost/myapp/?",
      "pos": [
        9933,
        10067
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "error=access_denied\n&amp;error_description=the+user+canceled+the+authentication\n```\n\n| Parameter | Description |\n| ----------------------- | ------------------------------- |\n| error | An error code string that can be used to classify types of errors that occur, and can be used to react to errors.",
      "pos": [
        10068,
        10362
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| error_description | A specific error message that can help a developer identify the root cause of an authentication error.",
      "pos": [
        10363,
        10489
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n\n#### Request an Access Token\nNow that you've acquired an authorization_code and have been granted permission by the user, you can redeem the <ph id=\"ph1\">`code`</ph> for an <ph id=\"ph2\">`access_token`</ph> to the desired resource, by sending a <ph id=\"ph3\">`POST`</ph> request to the <ph id=\"ph4\">`/token`</ph> endpoint:\n\n```\nPOST common/v2.0/oauth2/token HTTP/1.1\nHost: https://login.microsoftonline.com\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n{\n    \"grant_type\": \"authorization_code\",\n    \"client_id\": \"2d4d11a2-f814-46a7-890a-274a72a7309e\",\n    \"scope\": \"https://graph.windows.net/directory.read https://graph.windows.net/directory.write\",\n    \"code\": \"AwABAAAAvPM1KaPlrEqdFSBzjqfTGBCmLdgfSTLEMPGYuNHSUYBrq...\"",
      "pos": [
        10491,
        11127
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "\"client_secret\": \"zc53fwe80980293klaj9823\"  // NOTE: Only required for web apps\n}\n```\n\n| Parameter | | Description |\n| ----------------------- | ------------------------------- | --------------------- |\n| client_id | required | The Application Id that the registration portal (<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">apps.dev.microsoft.com](https://apps.dev.microsoft.com)</ept>) assigned your app.",
      "pos": [
        11132,
        11485
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| grant_type | required | Must be <ph id=\"ph1\">`authorization_code`</ph> for the authorization code flow.",
      "pos": [
        11486,
        11575
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| scope | required | A space-separated list of scopes.",
      "pos": [
        11576,
        11632
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The scopes requested in this leg must be equivalent to or a subset of the scopes requested in the first leg.",
      "pos": [
        11634,
        11742
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If the scopes specified in this request span multiple resource servers, then the v2.0 endpoint will return a token for the resource specified in the first scope.",
      "pos": [
        11744,
        11905
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For a more detailed explanation of scopes, refer to <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">permissions, consent, and scopes](active-directory-v2-scopes.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        11907,
        12025
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| code | required | The authorization_code that you acquired in the first leg of the flow.",
      "pos": [
        12027,
        12119
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| client_secret | required for web apps | The application secret that you created in the app registration portal for your app.",
      "pos": [
        12122,
        12250
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It should not be used in a native  app, because client_secrets cannot be reliably stored on devices.",
      "pos": [
        12252,
        12352
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It is required for web apps and web APIs, which have the ability to store the client_secret securely on the server side.",
      "pos": [
        12354,
        12474
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n\nA successful token response will look like:\n\n```\n{\n    \"access_token\": \"eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsIng1dCI6Ik5HVEZ2ZEstZnl0aEV1Q...\",\n    \"token_type\": \"Bearer\",\n    \"expires_in\": \"3600\",\n    \"expires_on\": \"1388444763\",\n    \"scope\": \"https://graph.windows.net/directory.read https://graph.windows.net/directory.write\",\n    \"refresh_token\": \"AwABAAAAvPM1KaPlrEqdFSBzjqfTGAMxZGUTdM0t4B4...\",\n    \"id_token\": \"eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJub25lIn0.eyJhdWQiOiIyZDRkMTFhMi1mODE0LTQ2YTctOD...\"",
      "pos": [
        12475,
        12972
      ]
    },
    {
