      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| error_description | A specific error message that can help a developer identify the root cause of an authentication error.",
      "pos": [
        14648,
        14774
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n\n#### Use the Access Token\nNow that you've successfully acquired an <ph id=\"ph1\">`access_token`</ph>, you can use the token in reqeusts to Web APIs by including it in the <ph id=\"ph2\">`Authorization`</ph> header:\n\n```\nGET /contoso.onmicrosoft.com/users\nHost: https://graph.windows.net\nAuthorization: Bearer eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsIng1dCI6Ik5HVEZ2ZEstZnl0aEV1Q...\n```\n\n#### Refresh the Access Token\nAccess_tokens are short lived, and you must refresh them after they expire to continue accessing resources.",
      "pos": [
        14776,
        15260
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can do so by submitting another <ph id=\"ph1\">`POST`</ph> request to the <ph id=\"ph2\">`/authorize`</ph> endpoint, this time providing the <ph id=\"ph3\">`refresh_token`</ph> instead of the <ph id=\"ph4\">`code`</ph>:\n\n```\nPOST common/v2.0/oauth2/token HTTP/1.1\nHost: https://login.microsoftonline.com\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n{\n    \"grant_type\": \"refresh_token\",\n    \"client_id\": \"2d4d11a2-f814-46a7-890a-274a72a7309e\",\n    \"scope\": \"https://graph.windows.net/directory.read https://graph.windows.net/directory.write\",\n    \"refresh_token\": \"AwABAAAAvPM1KaPlrEqdFSBzjqfTGBCmLdgfSTLEMPGYuNHSUYBrq...\",\n    \"client_secret\": \"zc53fwe80980293klaj9823\"  // NOTE: Only required for web apps\n}\n```\n\n| Parameter | | Description |\n| ----------------------- | ------------------------------- | -------- |\n| client_id | required | The Application Id that the registration portal (<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">apps.dev.microsoft.com](https://apps.dev.microsoft.com)</ept>) assigned your app.",
      "pos": [
        15262,
        16140
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| grant_type | required | Must be <ph id=\"ph1\">`refresh_token`</ph> for this leg of the authorization code flow.",
      "pos": [
        16141,
        16237
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| scope | required | A space-separated list of scopes.",
      "pos": [
        16238,
        16294
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The scopes requested in this leg must be equivalent to or a subset of the scopes requested in the original authorization_code request leg.",
      "pos": [
        16296,
        16434
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If the scopes specified in this request span multiple resource servers, then the v2.0 endpoint will return a token for the resource specified in the first scope.",
      "pos": [
        16436,
        16597
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For a more detailed explanation of scopes, refer to <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">permissions, consent, and scopes](active-directory-v2-scopes.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        16599,
        16717
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| refresh_token | required | The refresh_token that you acquired in the second leg of the flow.",
      "pos": [
        16719,
        16816
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| client_secret | required for web apps | The application secret that you created in the app registration portal for your app.",
      "pos": [
        16819,
        16947
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It should not be used in a native  app, because client_secrets cannot be reliably stored on devices.",
      "pos": [
        16949,
        17049
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It is required for web apps and web APIs, which have the ability to store the client_secret securely on the server side.",
      "pos": [
        17051,
        17171
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n\nA successful token response will look like:\n\n```\n{\n    \"access_token\": \"eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsIng1dCI6Ik5HVEZ2ZEstZnl0aEV1Q...\",\n    \"token_type\": \"Bearer\",\n    \"expires_in\": \"3600\",\n    \"expires_on\": \"1388444763\",\n    \"scope\": \"https://graph.windows.net/directory.read https://graph.windows.net/directory.write\",\n    \"refresh_token\": \"AwABAAAAvPM1KaPlrEqdFSBzjqfTGAMxZGUTdM0t4B4...\",\n    \"id_token\": \"eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJub25lIn0.eyJhdWQiOiIyZDRkMTFhMi1mODE0LTQ2YTctOD...\"",
      "pos": [
        17172,
        17669
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "}\n```\n| Parameter | Description |\n| ----------------------- | ------------------------------- |\n| access_token | The requested access token.",
      "pos": [
        17670,
        17810
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The  app can use this token to authenticate to the secured resource, such as a web API.",
      "pos": [
        17811,
        17898
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| token_type | Indicates the token type value.",
      "pos": [
        17899,
        17947
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The only type that Azure AD supports is Bearer  |\n| expires_in | How long the access token is valid (in seconds).",
      "pos": [
        17948,
        18061
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| expires_on | The time when the access token expires.",
      "pos": [
        18062,
        18118
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The date is represented as the number of seconds from the epoch time.",
      "pos": [
        18119,
        18188
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| scope | The scopes that the access_token is valid for.",
      "pos": [
        18189,
        18247
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| refresh_token |  A new OAuth 2.0 refresh token.",
      "pos": [
        18248,
        18299
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You should replace the old refresh token with this newly acquired refresh token to ensure your refresh tokens remain valid for as long as possible.",
      "pos": [
        18300,
        18447
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| id_token | An unsigned JSON Web Token (JWT).",
      "pos": [
        18449,
        18497
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The  app can base64Url decode the segements of this token to request information about the user who signed in.",
      "pos": [
        18498,
        18608
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The  app can cache the values and display them, but it should not rely on them for any authorization or security boundaries.",
      "pos": [
        18609,
        18733
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information about id_tokens see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">v2.0 app model token reference](active-directory-v2-tokens.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        18735,
        18844
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n\nError responses will look like:\n\n```\n{\n    \"error\": \"access_denied\",\n    \"error_description\": \"The user revoked access to the app.\",\n}\n```\n\n| Parameter | Description |\n| ----------------------- | ------------------------------- |\n| error | An error code string that can be used to classify types of errors that occur, and can be used to react to errors.",
      "pos": [
        18845,
        19201
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| error_description | A specific error message that can help a developer identify the root cause of an authentication error.",
      "pos": [
        19202,
        19328
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n\n\n\n\n\n\n## OpenID Connect Sign-In Flow\n<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">OpenID Connect](http://openid.net/specs/openid-connect-core-1_0.html)</ept> extends the OAuth 2.0 <bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>authorization<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept> protocol for use as an <bpt id=\"p3\">*</bpt>authentication<ept id=\"p3\">*</ept> protocol, which allows you to perform single sign-on using OAuth.",
      "pos": [
        19330,
        19583
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It introduces the concept of an <ph id=\"ph1\">`id_token`</ph>, which is a security token that allows the client to verify the identity of the user and obtain basic profile information about the user.",
      "pos": [
        19585,
        19765
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "OpenID Connect for the v2.0 app model is the recommended way to implement sign-in for a <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">web  app](active-directory-v2-flows.md#web-apps)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        19767,
        19905
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The most basic sign-in flow contains the following steps:\n\n<ph id=\"ph1\">![OpenId Connect Swimlanes](../media/active-directory-v2-flows/convergence_scenarios_webapp.png)</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">\n\n####</ph> Send the Sign-In Request\nWhen your web  app needs to authenticate the user, it can direct the user to the <ph id=\"ph3\">`/authorize`</ph> endpoint.",
      "pos": [
        19907,
        20197
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This request is similar to the first leg of the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">OAuth 2.0 Authorization Code Flow](#oauth2-authorization-code-flow)</ept>, with a few important distinctions:\n- The request must include the scope <ph id=\"ph1\">`openid`</ph> in the <ph id=\"ph2\">`scope`</ph> parameter.",
      "pos": [
        20199,
        20423
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "- The <ph id=\"ph1\">`response_type`</ph> parameter must include <ph id=\"ph2\">`id_token`</ph><ph id=\"ph3\">\n-</ph> The request must include the <ph id=\"ph4\">`nonce`</ph> parameter\n\n```\nGET https://login.microsoftonline.com/common/oauth2/v2.0/authorize?",
      "pos": [
        20424,
        20601
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "client_id=2d4d11a2-f814-46a7-890a-274a72a7309e      // Your registered Application Id\n&amp;response_type=id_token\n&amp;redirect_uri=http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%2Fmyapp%2F       // Your registered Redirect Uri, url encoded\n&amp;response_mode=query                                  // 'query', 'form_post', or 'fragment'\n&amp;scope=openid                                        // Translates to the 'Read your profile' permission\n&amp;state=12345                                         // Any value, provided by your app\n&amp;nonce=678910                                        // Any value, provided by your app\n```\n\n| Parameter | | Description |\n| ----------------------- | ------------------------------- | --------------- |\n| client_id | required | The Application Id that the registration portal (<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">apps.dev.microsoft.com](https://apps.dev.microsoft.com)</ept>) assigned your app.",
      "pos": [
        20602,
        21450
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| response_type | required | Must include <ph id=\"ph1\">`id_token`</ph> for OpenID Connect sign-in.",
      "pos": [
        21451,
        21533
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It may also include other response_types, as described in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">OpenID Connect with OAuth Code Flow ](#OpenID-Connect-with-OAuth-Code-Flow)</ept> section.",
      "pos": [
        21535,
        21682
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| redirect_uri | required | The redirect_uri of your app, where authentication responses can be sent and received by your app.",
      "pos": [
        21683,
        21811
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It must exactly match one of the redirect_uris you registered in the portal, except it must be url encoded.",
      "pos": [
        21813,
        21920
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| scope | required | A space-separated list of scopes.",
      "pos": [
        21921,
        21977
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For OpenID Connect, it must include the scope <ph id=\"ph1\">`openid`</ph>, which translates to the \"Sign in &amp; Read Your Profile\" permission in the consent UI.",
      "pos": [
        21979,
        22118
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You may also include other scopes in this request for requesting consent, as described in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">OpenID Connect with OAuth Code Flow ](#OpenID-Connect-with-OAuth-Code-Flow)</ept> section.",
      "pos": [
        22120,
        22299
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| nonce | required | A value included in the request, generated by the app, that will included in the resulting id_token as a claim.",
      "pos": [
        22301,
        22435
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The app can then verify this value to mitigate token replay attacks.",
      "pos": [
        22437,
        22505
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The value is typically a randomized, unique string that can be used to identify the origin of the request.",
      "pos": [
        22507,
        22613
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| response_mode | recommended | Specifies the method that should be used to send the resulting authorization_code back to your app.",
      "pos": [
        22615,
        22748
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Can be one of 'query', 'form_post', or 'fragment'.",
      "pos": [
        22750,
        22800
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "| state | recommended | A value included in the request that will also be returned in the token response.",
      "pos": [
        22803,
        22908
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It can be a string of any content that you wish.",
      "pos": [
        22910,
        22958
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A randomly generated unique value is typically used for preventing cross-site request forgery attacks.",
      "pos": [
        22960,
        23062
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The state is also used to encode information about the user's state in the app before the authentication request occurred, such as the page or view they were on.",
      "pos": [
        23064,
        23225
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| prompt | optional | Indicates the type of user interaction that is required.",
      "pos": [
        23226,
        23306
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The only valid value at this time is 'login', which forces the user to enter their credentials on that request.",
      "pos": [
        23308,
        23419
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Single-sign on will not take effect.",
      "pos": [
        23421,
        23457
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n\nAt this point, the user will be asked to enter their credentials and complete the authentication.",
      "pos": [
        23458,
        23558
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The v2.0 endpoint will also ensure that the user has consented to the permissions indicated in the <ph id=\"ph1\">`scope`</ph> query parameter.",
      "pos": [
        23560,
        23683
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If the user has not consented to any of those permissions, it will ask the user to consent to the required permissions.",
      "pos": [
        23685,
        23804
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Details of <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">permissions, consent, and multi-tenant apps are provided here](active-directory-v2-scopes.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        23806,
        23912
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Once the user authenticates and grants consent, the v2.0 endpoint will return a response to your app at the indicated <ph id=\"ph1\">`redirect_uri`</ph>, using the method specified in the <ph id=\"ph2\">`response_mode`</ph> parameter.",
      "pos": [
        23914,
        24108
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A successful response using <ph id=\"ph1\">`response_mode=query`</ph> looks like:\n\n```\nGET https://localhost/myapp/?",
      "pos": [
        24110,
        24206
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "id_token=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsIng1dCI6Ik5HVEZ2ZEstZnl0aEV1Q...   // the id_token, truncated\n&amp;session_state=7B29111D-C220-4263-99AB-6F6E135D75EF            // a value generated by the v2.0 endpoint\n&amp;state=12345                                                    // the value provided in the request\n\n```\n\n| Parameter | Description |\n| ----------------------- | ------------------------------- |\n| id_token | The id_token that the  app requested.",
      "pos": [
        24207,
        24666
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can use the id_token to verify the user's identity and begin a session with the user.",
      "pos": [
        24667,
        24756
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "More details on id_tokens and their contents is included in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">v2.0 endpoint token reference](active-directory-v2-tokens.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        24758,
        24885
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| session_state | A unique value that identifies the current user session.",
      "pos": [
        24887,
        24963
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This value is a GUID, but should be treated as an opaque value that is passed without examination.",
      "pos": [
        24964,
        25062
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| state | If a state parameter is included in the request, the same value should appear in the response.",
      "pos": [
        25063,
        25169
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The  app should verify that the state values in the request and response are identical.",
      "pos": [
        25170,
        25257
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n\nError responses may also be sent to the <ph id=\"ph1\">`redirect_uri`</ph> so the app can handle them appropriately:\n\n```\nGET https://localhost/myapp/?",
      "pos": [
        25258,
        25392
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "error=access_denied\n&amp;error_description=the+user+canceled+the+authentication\n```\n\n| Parameter | Description |\n| ----------------------- | ------------------------------- |\n| error | An error code string that can be used to classify types of errors that occur, and can be used to react to errors.",
      "pos": [
        25393,
        25687
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n| error_description | A specific error message that can help a developer identify the root cause of an authentication error.",
      "pos": [
        25688,
        25814
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "|\n\n#### Validate the id_token\nJust receiving an id_token is not sufficient to authenticate the user; you must validate the id_token's signature and verify the claims in the token per your  app's requirements.",
      "pos": [
        25816,
        26024
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The v2.0 endpoint uses <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">JSON Web Tokens (JWTs)](http://self-issued.info/docs/draft-ietf-oauth-json-web-token.html)</ept> and public key cryptography to sign tokens and verify that they are valid.",
      "pos": [
        26026,
        26215
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The v2.0 app model has an OpenID Connect metadata endpoint, which allows an app to fetch information about the v2.0 app model at runtime.",
      "pos": [
        26217,
        26354
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This information includes endpoints, token contents, and token signing keys.",
      "pos": [
        26356,
        26432
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The metadata endpoint contains a JSON document located at:\n\n<ph id=\"ph1\">`https://login.microsoftonline.com/common/v2.0/.well-known/configuration`</ph>\n\nOne of the properties of this configuration document is the <ph id=\"ph2\">`jwks_uri`</ph>, whose value for the v2.0 app model will be:\n\n<ph id=\"ph3\">`https://login.microsoftonline.com/common/discovery/v2.0/keys`</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        26434,
        26749
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can use the RSA256 public keys located at this endpoint to validate the signature of the id_token.",
      "pos": [
        26751,
        26853
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There are multiple keys listed at this endpoint at any given point in time, each identified by a <ph id=\"ph1\">`kid`</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        26855,
        26958
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The header of the id_token also contains a <ph id=\"ph1\">`kid`</ph> claim, which indicates which of these keys was used to sign the id_token.",
      "pos": [
        26960,
        27082
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "See the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">v2.0 app model token reference](active-directory-v2-tokens.md)</ept> for more information, including <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p2\">Validating Tokens](active-directory-v2-tokens.md#validating-tokens)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p3\">Important Information About Signing Key Rollover](active-directory-v2-tokens.md#validating-tokens)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        27086,
        27363
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Once you've validated the signature of the id_token, there are a few claims you will need to verify:",
      "pos": [
        27410,
        27510
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You should validate the <ph id=\"ph1\">`nonce`</ph> claim to prevent token replay attacks.",
      "pos": [
        27514,
        27584
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Its value should be what you specified in the sign-in request.",
      "pos": [
        27586,
        27648
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You should validate the <ph id=\"ph1\">`aud`</ph> claim to ensure the id_token was issued for your app.",
      "pos": [
        27651,
        27734
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Its value should be the <ph id=\"ph1\">`client_id`</ph> of your app.",
      "pos": [
        27736,
        27784
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        27787,
        27873
      ],
      "content": "You should validate the <ph id=\"ph1\">`iat`</ph> and <ph id=\"ph2\">`exp`</ph> claims to ensure the id_token has not expired."
    },
    {
      "content": "You may also wish to validate additional claims depending on your scenario.",
      "pos": [
        27875,
        27950
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Some common validations include:",
      "pos": [
        27952,
        27984
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Ensuring the user/organization has signed up for the  app.",
      "pos": [
        27988,
        28046
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Ensuring the user has proper authorization/privileges",
      "pos": [
        28049,
        28102
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Ensuring a certain strength of authentication has occurred, such as multi-factor authentication.",
      "pos": [
        28105,
        28201
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        28203,
        28326
      ],
      "content": "For more information on the claims in an id_token, see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>v2.0 app model token reference<ept id=\"p1\">](active-directory-v2-tokens.md)</ept>."
    },
    {
      "content": "Once you have completely validated the id_token, you can begin a session with the user and use the claims in the id_token to obtain information about the user in your app.",
      "pos": [
        28328,
        28499
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This information can be used for display, records, authorizations, etc.",
      "pos": [
        28501,
        28572
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Send a Sign Out Request",
      "pos": [
        28579,
        28602
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The OpenIdConnect <ph id=\"ph1\">`end_session_endpoint`</ph> is not currently supported by the v2.0 app model preview.",
      "pos": [
        28604,
        28702
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This means your app cannot send a request to the v2.0 endpoint to end a user's session and clear cookies set by the v2.0 endpoint.",
      "pos": [
        28703,
        28833
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To sign a user out, your app can simply end its own session with the user, and leave the user's session with the v2.0 endpoint in-tact.",
      "pos": [
        28834,
        28969
      ]
